{"word":"ἐύς","slug":"ἐύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐύς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>epic <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>ἠΰ</el> (<a href='S:εὖ'><el>εὖ</el></a> being used only as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>)\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:εὖ'><el>εὖ</el></a>\n<p/><i>good, brave, noble</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—epic <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>ἐάων</el>, <i>of good things, good fortune</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/>"}]}